cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper proposes a probabilistic method for learning and inference of basic movements, which involves the use of a directed graphic model and deep generative model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the incorporation of task descriptors and context information for long-term planning, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The experimental validations involve robotic approaching path planning tasks, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY) sub-categories.
